<br>
Sam has been home for the past few weekends and has just a month or so left his his freshmen year at Washburn.  He has really taken to his first year at Wasburn and is very helpful when here.  Heidi has also been very helpful.  She has a little over a month left in her sophmore year and from the looks of her progress reports has kept her grades in focus.  While Heidi will drive herself to Easter services, Sam has to open at the golf course so Jaci and I will spend a quiet Easter at home.  Pastor Jay was able to drop in today, so we are using this as an excuse to sleep in tommorow!!  We will do a little grill tommorow afternoon before Sam heads back to Topeka.  <br>
<br>
Hope this update finds everyone in good health and again, to everyone, Jaci and I thank you for all the thoughts, prayers, visits, cards, flowers, meals, e-mails, and forum messages.  We are looking for some very beautiful walks in the coming days as mother nature has provided a very refreshing uplift today in more ways than one.  Donna the flowers look beautiful and Herb the Birch trees are stunning!   How appropriate has the rain of today been so refreshing to the spirt of the moment in more ways than one!   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> marsha h</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/20/03 12:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Easter Sunday</span><hr size=1> Dear Dan and Jac,  Joel  is down so he checked my settings and things should be fine now.  <br>
I am so glad that Donna and Herb were able  to be there<br>
with you, and I feel that that time will always be precious to you and you can add them to the many happy times you have had already Hard to write this with so many other conversations going on here - we miss you.  Love Mom.  <br>
