 href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easter Greetings</span><hr size=1> My Easter was spent with my in-laws in Marshall.  I drove down with Karen, Joseph and Carl.  Tom stayed home with Sarah.  These teenagers sure have minds of their own!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Lots of rain means lots of green growth.  I'll enjoy the sun coming out, though, so that I can see all the spring changes.<br>
<br>
I talked to Mom and she reported that you all shared some smiles and laughter over the last two weeks.  That warmed my heart immeasureably, Jaci.  <br>
<br>
Love, Susan<br>
